The paper discusses the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for computer aided detection (CADe) in medical imaging, specifically for early stage lung cancer screening in chest x-rays. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of a genetic algorithm (GA) for neural architectural search (NAS), which falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of deep learning and CNNs also falls under the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of a large dataset and the evaluation of the model's performance, which falls under the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
